Maple Group’s Bertrand Says He Is ‘Comfortable’ Its TMX Bid Will Succeed

-- B y   S e a n   P a s t e r n a k   a n d   M a t t   W a l c o f f
-- 
2011-06-24T19:44:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-24/maple-group-s-bertrand-says-he-is-comfortable-its-tmx-bid-will-succeed.html
Maple Group Acquisition Corp. is
“comfortable with what we have now going into” TMX Group
Ltd.’s June 30 shareholder vote on London Stock Exchange Group
Plc’s rival bid for the company, Maple Group Chief Executive
Officer  Luc Bertrand  said.  Bertrand made the comments in an interview on Bloomberg
Television from Toronto in response to a question on whether
Maple Group may increase its C$3.73 billion ($3.78 billion) bid
for the Toronto Stock Exchange owner.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sean Pasternak in Toronto at 
 spasternak@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
